{"questionId":"9076866","questionHtml":"<p>L is a point source of light. The intensity of the light at a distance 2<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;from L is <em>I</em>. What is the&nbsp;intensity at a distance 3<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;from L?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{4}{9}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mn>9</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I</em></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{2}{3}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I</em></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{3}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I</em></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{9}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>9</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I</em></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076866","referenceCode":"18N.1.HL.TZ0.13","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"L is a point source of light. The intensity of the light at a distance 2 x from L is I. What is the intensity at a distance 3 x from L? A. 4 9 I B. 2 3 I C. 3 2 I D. 9 4 I","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"13","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.2 – Travelling waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}